                    </li>
                    <li>
                        216 owners have a different wire feed-through assembly than later years. You can still seal that assembly to the distributor per the instructions
                        below, however, you could be happier with the later assembly like <a href="http://www.steinertractor.com/ABC500-delco-distributor-terminal-insulator-square-shoulder" target=_blank>Here</a>.
                        It would make it easier to seal the parts together. You would have a little grinding to do on the plastic to make it fit, but maybe worth the trouble.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
            <div class="HowToTitle4">Choosing the proper Reluctor</div>
            <a href="http://images.devestechnet.com/Projects/HEIgnition/HEIProject0066lg.jpg">
                <img class="PicsLeft" img src="http://images.devestechnet.com/Projects/HEIgnition/HEIProject0066sm.jpg">
            </a>
            <a href="http://images.devestechnet.com/Projects/HEIgnition/DistributorDatalg.jpg">
                <img class="PicsRight" img src="http://images.devestechnet.com/Projects/HEIgnition/DistributorDatasm.jpg">
            </a>
            <p>
                GM made two different types of lobe contact areas depending on the year of your <b>Distributor</b>. Most of us enthusiasts purchased our vehicles from previous
                owners and we are not 100% certain that things have not been replaced along the way. To ensure you get the proper reluctor for your distributor, remove
